Q.What constraint prevents duplicate values?
Answer: UNIQUE constraint
Also:PRIMARY KEY also prevents duplicates (and NULL)

Q.Which index is better?

Query:WHERE status = 'SUCCESS' AND user_id = 101

Correct Answer:(user_id, status)
Why?

Index works left → right
First filter by user_id (high selectivity)
Then by status

If you use: (status, user_id)

Less efficient because status has fewer unique 
values

Q.When should you NOT use index?

Avoid index when:

Table is small
Column has low uniqueness (e.g., gender)
Too many INSERT/UPDATE operations
Column frequently updated

Q.Why too many indexes are bad?

Because:

Slow INSERT/UPDATE (index needs update)
More storage used
Query planner confusion
